    "summary": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Two alternative statements are held to be the only possible options when in reality there are more.",
        "spans": []
      }
    ],
    "description": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "The Black-or-White Fallacy occurs in arguments that have a disjunctive premise―that is, one that gives alternatives―when one or more alternatives is incorrectly omitted. The fallacy tries to force you to choose either black or white when grey is an available alternative.",
