    "examples": [
      {
        "example": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "Gerda Reith is convinced that superstition can be a positive force. \"It gives you a sense of control by making you think you can work out what's going to happen next,\" she says. \"And it also makes you feel lucky. And to take a risk or to enter into a chancy situation, you really have to believe in your own luck. In that sense, it's a very useful way of thinking, because the alternative is fatalism, which is to say, 'Oh, there's nothing I can do.' At least superstition makes people do things.\"",
